MacroAsia Corp., SM, Trans-Asia Oil: Philippines Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-07-04T00:36:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/macroasia-corp-sm-trans-asia-oil-philippines-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1.4 percent to
4,351.63.  MacroAsia Corp. (MAC)  : The Philippine provider of in-
flight catering services will get $4.77 million as shares in the
cash dividend that its 49 percent owned venture Lufthansa
Technik Philippines will pay, a stock exchange filing showed.
The stock decreased 0.7 percent to 3 pesos.  SM Investments Corp. (SM)  : The holding company of
Philippine billionaire  Henry Sy  approved a $142.2 million
investment in  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development (AT)  Corp, a stock exchange filing showed. SM was unchanged at 534.50
pesos. Atlas climbed 2.7 percent to 21.25 pesos.  Trans-Asia Oil & Energy Development (TA)  Corp: The
Philippine oil explorer and energy company won approval from the
 Department of Energy  to transfer an 8.18 percent stake in a
project to NorAsian Energy Ltd., a stock exchange filing showed.
NorAsia will assume Trans-Asia’s share in the project’s first
and second second well, it said. The stock decreased 3.4 percent
to 1.13 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
